===Etymology===
{{NL.}} term '''[[anarchia]]''' < {{AGr.}} '''{{polytonic|[[ἀναρχία]]}}''' (anarchia) < '''{{polytonic|[[ἀν-]]}}''' (a-) "not", + '''[[ἀρχός]]''' (archos) "ruler", "authority".

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ˈænərki/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|anarchies|-}}

# The state of a society being without [[authoritarians]] or a [[govern]]ing body.
# A [[chaotic]] and confusing [[absence]] of any form of [[political]] [[authority]] or [[government]].
# [[anarchism|Anarchism]]; the political [[theory]] that a [[community]] is best [[organize|organized]] by [[voluntary]] [[cooperation]] of [[individual]]s, rather than by [[coercive]] [[government]]. 

====Usage notes====
*Anarchists feel it is inappropriate to use the word “anarchy” to mean "a state of chaos or confusion". However, many non-anarchists do use it that way.

